originalText.text: In five weeks, following Dr. Craig Antell’s directions , I was able to be free from the excruciating pain which overpassed my labor pain to no pain at all; he and his team brought me back from crippled to a human being condition again. Hope in the next 6 weeks for my follow-up appointment I could be back to my old self.  The key of success is to stay with the program and complete the entire treatment requested by Dr. Craig Antell.  Due to my condition, I would have to maintain lifelong contact with Dr Antell to keep myself upright and enjoy my life. Having my residence on Staten Island I’m blessed with the 5 miles of the fantastic shore line. Hope to be able to walk long distance again to keep-up with the New York lifestyle.

originalText.text: Went to see the doctor for pain in my arm. It was Friday evening. Dr. said his nurse was taken ill and was absent that day. He was supposed to give me places of recommendation for physical therapy of my arm and said his nurse would call the following Monday. She never did. Had to follow up 2 times myself phoning them, waiting on the phone for them. After a week the nurse calls, doesn't really give me places I could go to, doesn't even tell me in detail what I need to say to whoever I go visit. She gave me a number for NYU near where I lived, and says everything is in the notes of the doctor. When I look at MyChart, there is nothing. Not even sure who to talk to. I don't have time to keep chasing. Unprofessional.
